          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The interaction of high energy neutrons with matter",
                "seems to be largely one of approximately elastic",
                "collisions with atomic nuclei, resulting in",
                "scattering of the neutrons. The scattering of",
                "neutrons has been studied using interposed",
                "cylindrical specimens to scatter neutrons away from",
                "the ionization chamber, and using toroidal specimens",
                "to scatter neutrons into the ionization chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Th collision areas computed from the scattering",
                "measurements increase with atomic weight in a manner",
                "that indicates that the effective volume of the",
                "nucleus is proportional to its atomic weight, but the",
                "classical elastic sphere collision theory is",
                "inadequate,and a wave theory of scattering must be",
                "used to obtain consistent quantitative results."
              ]
            }
          ],
